Colombia Stocks: Ecopetrol, Textiles Fabricato, Gruposura Rise

-- B y   B l a k e   S c h m i d t
-- 
2011-05-06T14:44:02Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-06/colombia-stocks-ecopetrol-textiles-fabricato-gruposura-rise.html
The following companies are having
unusual price changes in Bogota trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of 10:26 a.m. New York time.  The IGBC Index rose 1.2 percent to 13,929.58, while the
Colcap Index gained 1 percent to 1,659.14, its biggest jump
since April 20.  Ecopetrol SA (ECOPETL)  , Colombia’s largest oil company,
rose 1.4 percent to 3,770 pesos. The state-run company said
yesterday that high crude prices have generated enough revenue
to fund its capital expenditures plan this year.  Chief Executive Officer Javier Gutierrez said yesterday on
a conference call that the company is waiting for “the proper
moment” to issue shares this year of as much as a 9.9 percent
stake.  Textiles Fabricato Tejicondor SA (FABRI)  , Colombia’s
biggest textile maker, rose for a fifth day, its longest winning
streak since January. The stock gained 2.3 percent to 49.6
pesos, its highest level in almost four years, after U.S. House
of Representatives Speaker  John Boehner  said yesterday the house
hopes to pass a free-trade accord with Colombia by August,
Reuters reported.  Grupo de Inversiones Suramericana SA (GRUPOSUR)  , the
parent company of Colombia’s largest bank, climbed 1.3 percent
to 36,200 pesos after Standard & Poor’s gave the company an
international investment grade with a BBB- rating, according to
a regulatory filing yesterday.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Blake Schmidt in Bogota at 
